The [https://web.archive.org/web/20090302033447/http://baikal.arts.ualberta.ca/about/genetics.php ancient mtDNA] material obtained from human remains excavated from the Baikal region’s prehistoric cemeteries has demonstrated the genetic discontinuity between the Early Neolithic and Late Neolithic to Bronze Age peoples, the genetic similarity between the latter two, and has revealed new aspects of social and political complexity among the Early Neolithic groups.<ref name="Mooder et al. 2005">[http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6WH8-4FJD9D6-1&_user=10&_coverDate=04/01/2005&_rdoc=11&_fmt=high&_orig=browse&_srch=doc-info(%23toc%236844%232005%23999679995%23579295%23FLA%23display%23Volume)&_cdi=6844&_sort=d&_docanchor=&_ct=14&_acct=C000050221&_version=1&_urlVersion=0&_userid=10&md5=847ebdc8022523511155ac1ec3f63c20], '''Mooder, K.P., Weber, A.W., Schurr, T.G., Bamforth, F.J., Bazaliiskii, V.I., Savel’ev, N.A.''' 2005. Matrilinear Affinities and Prehistoric Siberian Mortuary Practices: A Case Study from Neolithic Lake Baikal. ''Journal of Archaeological Science'', vol. 32(4): 619–634.</ref><ref name="Mooder et al. 2006">[http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/112165015/abstract], '''Mooder, K.P., Schurr, T.G., Bamforth, F.J., Bazaliiski, V.I., Savel'ev, N.A.''' 2006. Population Affinities of Neolithic Siberians: A Snapshot from Prehistoric Lake Baikal. ''American Journal of Physical Anthropology'', vol. 129(3): 349–61.</ref> Examination of modern DNA materials in the context of the ancient DNA information allows assessment of the genetic history of native Siberians.<ref name="Schurr 2004">[http://arjournals.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev.anthro.33.070203.143932], '''Schurr, T. G.''' 2004. The Peopling of the New World: Perspectives from Molecular Anthropology. ''Annual Review of Anthropology'', vol. 33(3): 551–83.</ref><ref name="Schurr et al. 1999">[http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/30001797/abstract], '''Schurr, T. G.''', Sukernik R. I., Starikovskaya, E. B., Wallace, D. C. 1999. Mitochondrial DNA Diversity in Koryaks and Itel’men: Population Replacement in the Okhotsk-Bering Sea Region during the Neolithic. ''American Journal of Physical Anthropology'', vol. 108(1): 1–40.</ref><ref name="Gokcumen et al. 2008">[http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/117909241/abstract], Gokcumen, O., '''Dulik, M.C., Pai, A.A., Zhadanov, S.I., Osipova, L.P.''', Andreenkov, O., Tabikhanova, L., Gubina, M., '''Labuda, D., Schurr, T.G.''' 2008. Genetic Variation in the Enigmatic Altaian Kazakhs of South-Central Russia: Insights into Turkic Population History. American Journal of Physical Anthropology, vol. 136(3): 278–93.</ref>
[https://web.archive.org/web/20090302032014/http://baikal.arts.ualberta.ca/about/environmental.php Paleoenvironmental] research, which involves both extensive fieldwork and computer modeling techniques, has identified a period of climatic change affecting the Baikal region that coincided chronologically with the end of the Early Neolithic Kitoi culture.<ref name="Abzaeva et al. 2007">Abzaeva, A.A., '''Bezrukova, E.V.''', Bychinsky, V.A. et al. 2007. Struktura donnykh otlozhenii oz. Khubsugul: geologicheskii i klimaticheskii kontrol' [Structure of Bottom Sediments in Lake Hövsgöl: Geological and Climate Controls]. ''Geologiia i geofizika'', vol. 48: 863–85.</ref><ref name="Bezrukova et al. 2006">[http://www.springerlink.com/content/7n46325w40836v17/], '''Bezrukova, E.V.''', Belova, A., Abzaeva, A., Letunova, P., Orlova, L., Sokolova, L., Kulagina, N., Fisher, E. 2006. First High-Resolution Dated Records of Vegetation and Climate Changes on the Lake Baikal Northern Shore in the Middle–Late Holocene. ''Doklady Earth Sciences'' vol. 411(8): 1331–5.</ref><ref name="Bezrukova et al. 2008">[http://www.springerlink.com/content/yl8mt3j564nrwp20/?p=149863d576f04705a5288b8c84bca16b&pi=28], '''Bezrukova, E.V.''', Krivonogov, S., Takahara, H., Letunova, P., Shichi, K., Abzaeva, A., Kulagina, N. 2008. Lake Kotokel as a Stratotype for the Late Glacial and Holocene in Southeastern Siberia. ''Doklady Earth Sciences'', vol. 420(2): 658–64.</ref><ref name="Bush 2006">'''Bush, A.B.G.''' 2006. Temporal Variability of the South Asian Monsoon through the Late Quaternary: Results from AGCM and AOGCM Simulations. ''Journal of the Geological Society of India'', vol. 68(3): 533–44.</ref><ref name="Bush 2005">[http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6VGS-4F92400-2&_user=10&_coverDate=07/31/2005&_rdoc=4&_fmt=high&_orig=browse&_srch=doc-info(%23toc%236046%232005%23998639998%23593125%23FLA%23display%23Volume)&_cdi=6046&_sort=d&_docanchor=&_ct=14&_acct=C000050221&_version=1&_urlV