The '''Statement of 1000''' was a statement by 1000 Syrian intellectuals in January 2001, during the [[Damascus Spring]], following the earlier [[Statement of 99]] made in September 2000. The Statement of 1000 was more detailed than the earlier statement, criticising the effective one-party rule of the [[Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party – Syria Region|Ba'ath Party]] and calling for multiparty democracy, with an independent judiciary and without [[Human rights in Syria|discrimination against women]].<ref name="Wikas_Battling_Lion" />

