[[File:The Goodbye Family by Lorin Morgan-Richards.jpg|thumb|''The Goodbye Family'' by Lorin Morgan-Richards]] '''''The Goodbye Family''''' are a fictional family of [[undertaker]]s from the [[Weird West|Old Weird West]] of author and illustrator [[Lorin Morgan-Richards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scbwi.org/members-public/lorin-morgan-richards-2 |title=Public Profile |publisher=SCBWI |date=2014-10-15 |accessdate=2018-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://steamkat.com/goodbyeanniversary-2/ |title=An Interview with Lorin Morgan-Richards |publisher=SteamKat! |date=2016-11-28 |accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref> The Goodbye Family comprises Pyridine Goodbye, matriarch and [[mortician]], Otis, father and driver of the [[hearse]], their child Orphie, who has the dual role of [[gravedigger]] and self-appointed town Sheriff, and their pets: Ouiji the cat, a tarantula named Dorian, and Midnight their horse.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lorinrichards.com/GoodbyeFamily.html |title=Lorin Morgan-Richards - The Goodbye Family |publisher=Lorinrichards.com |date= |accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref>
Since 2009, the Goodbyes have appeared in both [[Panel (comics)|single panel comic]] and literature as part of the Great Mountain book series by Richards that begin with ''Me’ma and the Great Mountain''. The humor of the Goodbye Family is typically [[macabre]], often satirizing [[industrialization]] and rules of authority.
==Characters and story== Beginning in 2009, Richards started to produce the Goodbye Family as one-off cards after an inspiring trip to [[France]] and [[Wales]]. Richards envisioned Orphie, the daughter, and primary character, on the roof of the [[Notre Dame Cathedral]] sitting with gargoyles, while her parents Otis tried to board a train with a [[shrunken head]], and Pyridine publicly sewed a cadaver in Cardiff. Subsequent single panel comics and merchandise made of each character but before delving into their identities. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://americymru.blogspot.com/2010/08/ |title=AmeriCymru: 8/1/10 - 9/1/10 |publisher=Americymru.blogspot.com |date=2010-10-10 |accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref> In 2012, A Raven Above Press released Richards first novel ''[[Me’ma and the Great Mountain]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fictiondb.com/author/lorin-morgan-richards~mema-and-the-great-mountain~1556333~b.htm |title=Me'ma and the Great Mountain by Lorin Morgan-Richards |publisher=FictionDB |date= |accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Name |url=https://advicefromacaterpillar.wordpress.com/2012/04/26/review-mema-and-the-great-mountain/ |title=Review: Me’ma and the Great Mountain &#124; Advice from a Caterpillar |publisher=Advicefromacaterpillar.wordpress.com |date=2012-04-26 |accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref> about an indigenous girl that overcomes [[ghoul|ghoulish]] spirits to save her people. Along with her journey, she meets Hollis Sorrow, a friendly character entombed in a casket made by the Goodbye Family, marking the first mention in literature of the Goodbye Family. By 2015, Steamkat, an online comic distributor, weekly featured The Goodbye Family comic, and in the following year, Richards released subsequent book collections about the family.
* '''Orphie''': Daughter who loves mischief and has the strength of 20 men – which comes in handy when carrying caskets and as a gravedigger. She finds herself most often filling in as sheriff of the town and training her pet spider Dorian. * '''Otis''': Driver of their funeral hearse with an uncanny ability to smell demise a mile away. He is in charge of all the wakes. He spends his free time walking his hat and feeding their horse Midnight various pickled things. * '''Pyridine''': Matriarch and mortician of the family. She enjoys needling cadaviers and social gatherings with the undead. * '''Ouiji''': the family cat. Believed to be part [[Siamese cat|Siamese]] due to her glowing red eyes. * '''Dorian''': Orphie’s pet tarantula (specifically a Needlepoint Tarantula) that loves to spin webbed accessories for the family. * '''Midnight''': Most likely a [[Friesian horse]], she is the Goodbye's main implement of travel for both single rider and carriage. She characteristically is fueled by pickled things.
In an interview, when asked about the characters influences Richards replied: "I suppose Pyridine Goodbye, the matriarch, is loosely based on my wife, Otis Goodbye is myself, and Orphie their child is Berlin (Richards daughter) and our friend's child Heidi (who came before our daughter). All though with a few other influences. Just like the Goodbye Family we do have a pet tarantula and Siamese cat."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inspirationmatters.org/Interviewshow.aspx?name=Lorin+Morgan-Richards&id=76&totalrec=8&Alpha=L |title=Inspirational Story/Interview with Lorin Morgan-Richards |publisher=Inspirationmatters.org |date= |accessdate=2018-01-09}}</ref>
==Humor== Richards clarifies the genre of ''The Goodbye Family'': ''I fall into the category of [[Weird West]], but I think it may be more of a “Down West” as I’d like to call it, for its sense of macabre western humor.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newswhistle.com/the-dreaded-summons-our-qa-with-author-lorin-morgan-richards/ |title=The Dreaded Summons – Our Q&A with Author Lorin Morgan-Richards |publisher=NewsWhistle |date=2017-11-28 |accessdate=2018-03-15}}</ref>
